cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you cite this manuscript, its audit chain, or the
  reproducibility test suite, please cite as below.
title: >-
  An Organic Operator and AI Operator Collaborative Review of Active
  Inference Free Energy Minimization: Reviewable Foundations,
  Reproducible Tests, and Open Tensions
abstract: >-
  An audit-grade collaborative review of variational free energy as it
  is used in active inference, organized as a transparent re-presentation
  of the central variational identity together with a sentence-level
  provenance trail and a deterministic reproducibility test suite.
  Treats Maren's Themesis Technical Report TR-2019-01v6 ("Derivation
  of the Variational Bayes Equations") as a test case for the audit
  method, not a target. Layer 1 (AI-executable) of the audit remediation
  plan is complete; Layer 2 (human expert review) gates remain pending.
